37enum class Mode {
38 ALPHA,
39 LOWER,
40 MIXED,
41 PUNCT,
42 ALPHA_SHIFT,
43 PUNCT_SHIFT
44};
45
46static const int TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH = 900;
47static const int BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH = 901;
48static const int NUMERIC_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH = 902;
49static const int BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH_6 = 924;
50static const int ECI_USER_DEFINED = 925;
51static const int ECI_GENERAL_PURPOSE = 926;
52static const int ECI_CHARSET = 927;
53static const int BEGIN_MACRO_PDF417_CONTROL_BLOCK = 928;
54static const int BEGIN_MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD = 923;
55static const int MACRO_PDF417_TERMINATOR = 922;
56static const int MODE_SHIFT_TO_BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE = 913;
57static const int MAX_NUMERIC_CODEWORDS = 15;
58
59static const int MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD_FILE_NAME = 0;
60static const int MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD_SEGMENT_COUNT = 1;
61static const int MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD_TIME_STAMP = 2;
62static const int MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD_SENDER = 3;
63static const int MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD_ADDRESSEE = 4;
64static const int MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD_FILE_SIZE = 5;
65static const int MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD_CHECKSUM = 6;
66
67static const int PL = 25;
68static const int LL = 27;
69static const int AS = 27;
70static const int ML = 28;
71static const int AL = 28;
72static const int PS = 29;
73static const int PAL = 29;
74
75static const char* PUNCT_CHARS = ";<>@[\\]_`~!\r\t,:\n-.$/\"|*()?{}'";
76static const char* MIXED_CHARS = "0123456789&\r\t,:#-.$/+%*=^";
77static const CharacterSet DEFAULT_ENCODING = CharacterSet::ISO8859_1;
78
79static const int NUMBER_OF_SEQUENCE_CODEWORDS = 2;

82/**
83* The Text Compaction mode includes all the printable ASCII characters
84* (i.e. values from 32 to 126) and three ASCII control characters: HT or tab
85* (ASCII value 9), LF or line feed (ASCII value 10), and CR or carriage
86* return (ASCII value 13). The Text Compaction mode also includes various latch
87* and shift characters which are used exclusively within the mode. The Text
88* Compaction mode encodes up to 2 characters per codeword. The compaction rules
89* for converting data into PDF417 codewords are defined in 5.4.2.2. The sub-mode
90* switches are defined in 5.4.2.3.
91*
92* @param textCompactionData The text compaction data.
93* @param byteCompactionData The byte compaction data if there
94* was a mode shift.
95* @param length The size of the text compaction and byte compaction data.
96* @param result The decoded data is appended to the result.
97*/
98static void DecodeTextCompaction(const std::vector<int>& textCompactionData, const std::vector<int>& byteCompactionData, int length, std::string& result) {
99 // Beginning from an initial state of the Alpha sub-mode
100 // The default compaction mode for PDF417 in effect at the start of each symbol shall always be Text
101 // Compaction mode Alpha sub-mode (uppercase alphabetic). A latch codeword from another mode to the Text
102 // Compaction mode shall always switch to the Text Compaction Alpha sub-mode.
103 Mode subMode = Mode::ALPHA;
104 Mode priorToShiftMode = Mode::ALPHA;
105 int i = 0;
106 while (i < length) {
107 int subModeCh = textCompactionData[i];
108 char ch = 0;
109 switch (subMode) {
110 case Mode::ALPHA:
111 // Alpha (uppercase alphabetic)
112 if (subModeCh < 26) {
113 // Upper case Alpha Character
114 ch = (char)('A' + subModeCh);
115 }
116 else {
117 if (subModeCh == 26) {
118 ch = ' ';
119 }
120 else if (subModeCh == LL) {
121 subMode = Mode::LOWER;
122 }
123 else if (subModeCh == ML) {
124 subMode = Mode::MIXED;
125 }
126 else if (subModeCh == PS) {
127 // Shift to punctuation
128 priorToShiftMode = subMode;
129 subMode = Mode::PUNCT_SHIFT;
130 }
131 else if (subModeCh == MODE_SHIFT_TO_BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE) {
132 result.push_back((char)byteCompactionData[i]);
133 }
134 else if (subModeCh == TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH) {
135 subMode = Mode::ALPHA;
136 }
137 }
138 break;
139
140 case Mode::LOWER:
141 // Lower (lowercase alphabetic)
142 if (subModeCh < 26) {
143 ch = (char)('a' + subModeCh);
144 }
145 else {
146 if (subModeCh == 26) {
147 ch = ' ';
148 }
149 else if (subModeCh == AS) {
150 // Shift to alpha
151 priorToShiftMode = subMode;
152 subMode = Mode::ALPHA_SHIFT;
153 }
154 else if (subModeCh == ML) {
155 subMode = Mode::MIXED;
156 }
157 else if (subModeCh == PS) {
158 // Shift to punctuation
159 priorToShiftMode = subMode;
160 subMode = Mode::PUNCT_SHIFT;
161 }
162 else if (subModeCh == MODE_SHIFT_TO_BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE) {
163 // TODO Does this need to use the current character encoding? See other occurrences below
164 result.push_back((char)byteCompactionData[i]);
165 }
166 else if (subModeCh == TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH) {
167 subMode = Mode::ALPHA;
168 }
169 }
170 break;
171
172 case Mode::MIXED:
173 // Mixed (numeric and some punctuation)
174 if (subModeCh < PL) {
175 ch = MIXED_CHARS[subModeCh];
176 }
177 else {
178 if (subModeCh == PL) {
179 subMode = Mode::PUNCT;
180 }
181 else if (subModeCh == 26) {
182 ch = ' ';
183 }
184 else if (subModeCh == LL) {
185 subMode = Mode::LOWER;
186 }
187 else if (subModeCh == AL) {
188 subMode = Mode::ALPHA;
189 }
190 else if (subModeCh == PS) {
191 // Shift to punctuation
192 priorToShiftMode = subMode;
193 subMode = Mode::PUNCT_SHIFT;
194 }
195 else if (subModeCh == MODE_SHIFT_TO_BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE) {
196 result.push_back((char)byteCompactionData[i]);
197 }
198 else if (subModeCh == TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH) {
199 subMode = Mode::ALPHA;
200 }
201 }
202 break;
203
204 case Mode::PUNCT:
205 // Punctuation
206 if (subModeCh < PAL) {
207 ch = PUNCT_CHARS[subModeCh];
208 }
209 else {
210 if (subModeCh == PAL) {
211 subMode = Mode::ALPHA;
212 }
213 else if (subModeCh == MODE_SHIFT_TO_BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE) {
214 result.push_back((char)byteCompactionData[i]);
215 }
216 else if (subModeCh == TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH) {
217 subMode = Mode::ALPHA;
218 }
219 }
220 break;
221
222 case Mode::ALPHA_SHIFT:
223 // Restore sub-mode
224 subMode = priorToShiftMode;
225 if (subModeCh < 26) {
226 ch = (char)('A' + subModeCh);
227 }
228 else {
229 if (subModeCh == 26) {
230 ch = ' ';
231 }
232 else if (subModeCh == TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH) {
233 subMode = Mode::ALPHA;
234 }
235 }
236 break;
237
238 case Mode::PUNCT_SHIFT:
239 // Restore sub-mode
240 subMode = priorToShiftMode;
241 if (subModeCh < PAL) {
242 ch = PUNCT_CHARS[subModeCh];
243 }
244 else {
245 if (subModeCh == PAL) {
246 subMode = Mode::ALPHA;
247 }
248 else if (subModeCh == MODE_SHIFT_TO_BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE) {
249 // PS before Shift-to-Byte is used as a padding character,
250 // see 5.4.2.4 of the specification
251 result.push_back((char)byteCompactionData[i]);
252 }
253 else if (subModeCh == TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH) {
254 subMode = Mode::ALPHA;
255 }
256 }
257 break;
258 }
259 if (ch != 0) {
260 // Append decoded character to result
261 result.push_back(ch);
262 }
263 i++;
264 }
265}
266
267/**
268* Text Compaction mode (see 5.4.1.5) permits all printable ASCII characters to be
269* encoded, i.e. values 32 - 126 inclusive in accordance with ISO/IEC 646 (IRV), as
270* well as selected control characters.
271*
272* @param codewords The array of codewords (data + error)
273* @param codeIndex The current index into the codeword array.
274* @param result The decoded data is appended to the result.
275* @return The next index into the codeword array.
276*/
277static int TextCompaction(const std::vector<int>& codewords, int codeIndex, std::string& result)
278{
279 // 2 character per codeword
280 std::vector<int> textCompactionData((codewords[0] - codeIndex) * 2, 0);
281 // Used to hold the byte compaction value if there is a mode shift
282 std::vector<int> byteCompactionData((codewords[0] - codeIndex) * 2, 0);
283
284 int index = 0;
285 bool end = false;
286 while ((codeIndex < codewords[0]) && !end) {
287 int code = codewords[codeIndex++];
288 if (code < TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH) {
289 textCompactionData[index] = code / 30;
290 textCompactionData[index + 1] = code % 30;
291 index += 2;
292 }
293 else {
294 switch (code) {
295 case TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH:
296 // reinitialize text compaction mode to alpha sub mode
297 textCompactionData[index++] = TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH;
298 break;
299 case BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH:
300 case BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH_6:
301 case NUMERIC_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH:
302 case BEGIN_MACRO_PDF417_CONTROL_BLOCK:
303 case BEGIN_MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD:
304 case MACRO_PDF417_TERMINATOR:
305 codeIndex--;
306 end = true;
307 break;
308 case MODE_SHIFT_TO_BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE:
309 // The Mode Shift codeword 913 shall cause a temporary
310 // switch from Text Compaction mode to Byte Compaction mode.
311 // This switch shall be in effect for only the next codeword,
312 // after which the mode shall revert to the prevailing sub-mode
313 // of the Text Compaction mode. Codeword 913 is only available
314 // in Text Compaction mode; its use is described in 5.4.2.4.
315 textCompactionData[index] = MODE_SHIFT_TO_BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE;
316 code = codewords[codeIndex++];
317 byteCompactionData[index] = code;
318 index++;
319 break;
320 }
321 }
322 }
323 DecodeTextCompaction(textCompactionData, byteCompactionData, index, result);
324 return codeIndex;
325}
326

328/**
329* Byte Compaction mode (see 5.4.3) permits all 256 possible 8-bit byte values to be encoded.
330* This includes all ASCII characters value 0 to 127 inclusive and provides for international
331* character set support.
332*
333* @param mode The byte compaction mode i.e. 901 or 924
334* @param codewords The array of codewords (data + error)
335* @param encoding Currently active character encoding
336* @param codeIndex The current index into the codeword array.
337* @param result The decoded data is appended to the result.
338* @return The next index into the codeword array.
339*/
340static int ByteCompaction(int mode, const std::vector<int>& codewords, CharacterSet encoding, int codeIndex, std::wstring& result)
341{
342 ByteArray decodedBytes;
343 if (mode == BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH) {
344 // Total number of Byte Compaction characters to be encoded
345 // is not a multiple of 6
346 int count = 0;
347 int64_t value = 0;
348 std::array<int, 6> byteCompactedCodewords = {};
349 bool end = false;
350 int nextCode = codewords[codeIndex++];
351 while ((codeIndex < codewords[0]) && !end) {
352 byteCompactedCodewords[count++] = nextCode;
353 // Base 900
354 value = 900 * value + nextCode;
355 nextCode = codewords[codeIndex++];
356 // perhaps it should be ok to check only nextCode >= TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH
357 if (nextCode == TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH ||
358 nextCode == BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH ||
359 nextCode == NUMERIC_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH ||
360 nextCode == BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH_6 ||
361 nextCode == BEGIN_MACRO_PDF417_CONTROL_BLOCK ||
362 nextCode == BEGIN_MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD ||
363 nextCode == MACRO_PDF417_TERMINATOR) {
364 codeIndex--;
365 end = true;
366 }
367 else {
368 if ((count % 5 == 0) && (count > 0)) {
369 // Decode every 5 codewords
370 // Convert to Base 256
371 for (int j = 0; j < 6; ++j) {
372 decodedBytes.push_back((uint8_t)(value >> (8 * (5 - j))));
373 }
374 value = 0;
375 count = 0;
376 }
377 }
378 }
379
380 // if the end of all codewords is reached the last codeword needs to be added
381 if (codeIndex == codewords[0] && nextCode < TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH) {
382 byteCompactedCodewords[count++] = nextCode;
383 }
384
385 // If Byte Compaction mode is invoked with codeword 901,
386 // the last group of codewords is interpreted directly
387 // as one byte per codeword, without compaction.
388 for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
389 decodedBytes.push_back((uint8_t)byteCompactedCodewords[i]);
390 }
391
392 }
393 else if (mode == BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH_6) {
394 // Total number of Byte Compaction characters to be encoded
395 // is an integer multiple of 6
396 int count = 0;
397 int64_t value = 0;
398 bool end = false;
399 while (codeIndex < codewords[0] && !end) {
400 int code = codewords[codeIndex++];
401 if (code < TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH) {
402 count++;
403 // Base 900
404 value = 900 * value + code;
405 }
406 else {
407 if (code == TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH ||
408 code == BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH ||
409 code == NUMERIC_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH ||
410 code == BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH_6 ||
411 code == BEGIN_MACRO_PDF417_CONTROL_BLOCK ||
412 code == BEGIN_MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD ||
413 code == MACRO_PDF417_TERMINATOR) {
414 codeIndex--;
415 end = true;
416 }
417 }
418 if ((count % 5 == 0) && (count > 0)) {
419 // Decode every 5 codewords
420 // Convert to Base 256
421 for (int j = 0; j < 6; ++j) {
422 decodedBytes.push_back((uint8_t)(value >> (8 * (5 - j))));
423 }
424 value = 0;
425 count = 0;
426 }
427 }
428 }
429 TextDecoder::Append(result, decodedBytes.data(), Size(decodedBytes), encoding);
430 return codeIndex;
431}

434/**
435* Convert a list of Numeric Compacted codewords from Base 900 to Base 10.
436*
437* @param codewords The array of codewords
438* @param count The number of codewords
439* @return The decoded string representing the Numeric data.
440*/
441/*
442EXAMPLE
443Encode the fifteen digit numeric string 000213298174000
444Prefix the numeric string with a 1 and set the initial value of
445t = 1 000 213 298 174 000
446Calculate codeword 0
447d0 = 1 000 213 298 174 000 mod 900 = 200
448
449t = 1 000 213 298 174 000 div 900 = 1 111 348 109 082
450Calculate codeword 1
451d1 = 1 111 348 109 082 mod 900 = 282
452
453t = 1 111 348 109 082 div 900 = 1 234 831 232
454Calculate codeword 2
455d2 = 1 234 831 232 mod 900 = 632
456
457t = 1 234 831 232 div 900 = 1 372 034
458Calculate codeword 3
459d3 = 1 372 034 mod 900 = 434
460
461t = 1 372 034 div 900 = 1 524
462Calculate codeword 4
463d4 = 1 524 mod 900 = 624
464
465t = 1 524 div 900 = 1
466Calculate codeword 5
467d5 = 1 mod 900 = 1
468t = 1 div 900 = 0
469Codeword sequence is: 1, 624, 434, 632, 282, 200
470
471Decode the above codewords involves
4721 x 900 power of 5 + 624 x 900 power of 4 + 434 x 900 power of 3 +
473632 x 900 power of 2 + 282 x 900 power of 1 + 200 x 900 power of 0 = 1000213298174000
474
475Remove leading 1 => Result is 000213298174000
476*/
477static DecodeStatus DecodeBase900toBase10(const std::vector<int>& codewords, int count, std::string& resultString)
478{
479 // Table containing values for the exponent of 900.
480 static const auto EXP900 = []() {
481 std::array<BigInteger, 16> table = {1, 900};
482 for (size_t i = 2; i < table.size(); ++i) {
483 table[i] = table[i - 1] * 900;
484 }
485 return table;
486 }();
487
488 assert(count <= 16);
489
490 BigInteger result;
491 for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
492 result += EXP900[count - i - 1] * codewords[i];
493 }
494 resultString = result.toString();
495 if (!resultString.empty() && resultString.front() == '1') {
496 resultString = resultString.substr(1);
497 return DecodeStatus::NoError;
498 }
499 return DecodeStatus::FormatError;
500}

503/**
504* Numeric Compaction mode (see 5.4.4) permits efficient encoding of numeric data strings.
505*
506* @param codewords The array of codewords (data + error)
507* @param codeIndex The current index into the codeword array.
508* @param result The decoded data is appended to the result.
509* @return The next index into the codeword array.
510*/
511static DecodeStatus NumericCompaction(const std::vector<int>& codewords, int codeIndex, std::string& result, int& next)
512{
513 int count = 0;
514 bool end = false;
515
516 std::vector<int> numericCodewords(MAX_NUMERIC_CODEWORDS);
517
518 while (codeIndex < codewords[0] && !end) {
519 int code = codewords[codeIndex++];
520 if (codeIndex == codewords[0]) {
521 end = true;
522 }
523 if (code < TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH) {
524 numericCodewords[count] = code;
525 count++;
526 }
527 else {
528 if (code == TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH ||
529 code == BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH ||
530 code == BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH_6 ||
531 code == BEGIN_MACRO_PDF417_CONTROL_BLOCK ||
532 code == BEGIN_MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD ||
533 code == MACRO_PDF417_TERMINATOR) {
534 codeIndex--;
535 end = true;
536 }
537 }
538 if (count % MAX_NUMERIC_CODEWORDS == 0 || code == NUMERIC_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH || end) {
539 // Re-invoking Numeric Compaction mode (by using codeword 902
540 // while in Numeric Compaction mode) serves to terminate the
541 // current Numeric Compaction mode grouping as described in 5.4.4.2,
542 // and then to start a new one grouping.
543 if (count > 0) {
544 std::string tmp;
545 auto status = DecodeBase900toBase10(numericCodewords, count, tmp);
546 if (StatusIsError(status)) {
547 return status;
548 }
549 result += tmp;
550 count = 0;
551 }
552 }
553 }
554 next = codeIndex;
555 return DecodeStatus::NoError;
556}
557
558ZXING_EXPORT_TEST_ONLY
559DecodeStatus DecodeMacroBlock(const std::vector<int>& codewords, int codeIndex, DecoderResultExtra& resultMetadata, int& next)
560{
561 if (codeIndex + NUMBER_OF_SEQUENCE_CODEWORDS > codewords[0]) {
562 // we must have at least two bytes left for the segment index
563 return DecodeStatus::FormatError;
564 }
565 std::vector<int> segmentIndexArray(NUMBER_OF_SEQUENCE_CODEWORDS);
566 for (int i = 0; i < NUMBER_OF_SEQUENCE_CODEWORDS; i++, codeIndex++) {
567 segmentIndexArray[i] = codewords[codeIndex];
568 }
569
570 std::string strBuf;
571 DecodeStatus status = DecodeBase900toBase10(segmentIndexArray, NUMBER_OF_SEQUENCE_CODEWORDS, strBuf);
572 if (StatusIsError(status)) {
573 return status;
574 }
575
576 resultMetadata.setSegmentIndex(std::stoi(strBuf));
577
578 std::string fileId;
579 codeIndex = TextCompaction(codewords, codeIndex, fileId);
580 resultMetadata.setFileId(fileId);
581
582 int optionalFieldsStart = -1;
583 if (codewords[codeIndex] == BEGIN_MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD) {
584 optionalFieldsStart = codeIndex + 1;
585 }
586
587 while (codeIndex < codewords[0]) {
588 switch (codewords[codeIndex]) {
589 case BEGIN_MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD: {
590 codeIndex++;
591 switch (codewords[codeIndex]) {
592 case MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD_FILE_NAME: {
593 std::string fileName;
594 codeIndex = TextCompaction(codewords, codeIndex + 1, fileName);
595 resultMetadata.setFileName(fileName);
596 break;
597 }
598 case MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD_SENDER: {
599 std::string sender;
600 codeIndex = TextCompaction(codewords, codeIndex + 1, sender);
601 resultMetadata.setSender(sender);
602 break;
603 }
604 case MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD_ADDRESSEE: {
605 std::string addressee;
606 codeIndex = TextCompaction(codewords, codeIndex + 1, addressee);
607 resultMetadata.setAddressee(addressee);
608 break;
609 }
610 case MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD_SEGMENT_COUNT: {
611 std::string segmentCount;
612 status = NumericCompaction(codewords, codeIndex + 1, segmentCount, codeIndex);
613 resultMetadata.setSegmentCount(std::stoi(segmentCount));
614 break;
615 }
616 case MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD_TIME_STAMP: {
617 std::string timestamp;
618 status = NumericCompaction(codewords, codeIndex + 1, timestamp, codeIndex);
619 resultMetadata.setTimestamp(std::stoll(timestamp));
620 break;
621 }
622 case MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD_CHECKSUM: {
623 std::string checksum;
624 status = NumericCompaction(codewords, codeIndex + 1, checksum, codeIndex);
625 resultMetadata.setChecksum(std::stoi(checksum));
626 break;
627 }
628 case MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD_FILE_SIZE: {
629 std::string fileSize;
630 status = NumericCompaction(codewords, codeIndex + 1, fileSize, codeIndex);
631 resultMetadata.setFileSize(std::stoll(fileSize));
632 break;
633 }
634 default: {
635 status = DecodeStatus::FormatError;
636 break;
637 }
638 }
639 break;
640 }
641 case MACRO_PDF417_TERMINATOR: {
642 codeIndex++;
643 resultMetadata.setLastSegment(true);
644 break;
645 }
646 default: {
647 status = DecodeStatus::FormatError;
648 break;
649 }
650
651 if (StatusIsError(status)) {
652 return status;
653 }
654 }
655 }
656
657 // copy optional fields to additional options
658 if (optionalFieldsStart != -1) {
659 int optionalFieldsLength = codeIndex - optionalFieldsStart;
660 if (resultMetadata.isLastSegment()) {
661 // do not include terminator
662 optionalFieldsLength--;
663 }
664 resultMetadata.setOptionalData(std::vector<int>(codewords.begin() + optionalFieldsStart, codewords.begin() + optionalFieldsStart + optionalFieldsLength));
665 }
666
667 next = codeIndex;
668 return DecodeStatus::NoError;
669}
670
671DecoderResult
672DecodedBitStreamParser::Decode(const std::vector<int>& codewords, int ecLevel)
673{
674 std::wstring resultString;
675 auto encoding = DEFAULT_ENCODING;
676 // Get compaction mode
677 int codeIndex = 1;
678 int code = codewords[codeIndex++];
679 auto resultMetadata = std::make_shared<DecoderResultExtra>();
680 DecodeStatus status = DecodeStatus::NoError;
681 while (codeIndex < codewords[0] && status == DecodeStatus::NoError) {
682 switch (code) {
683 case TEXT_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH:
684 {
685 std::string buf;
686 codeIndex = TextCompaction(codewords, codeIndex, buf);
687 TextDecoder::AppendLatin1(resultString, buf);
688 break;
689 }
690 case BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH:
691 case BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH_6:
692 codeIndex = ByteCompaction(code, codewords, encoding, codeIndex, resultString);
693 break;
694 case MODE_SHIFT_TO_BYTE_COMPACTION_MODE:
695 resultString.push_back((wchar_t)codewords[codeIndex++]);
696 break;
697 case NUMERIC_COMPACTION_MODE_LATCH:
698 {
699 std::string buf;
700 status = NumericCompaction(codewords, codeIndex, buf, codeIndex);
701 TextDecoder::AppendLatin1(resultString, buf);
702 break;
703 }
704 case ECI_CHARSET:
705 encoding = CharacterSetECI::CharsetFromValue(codewords[codeIndex++]);
706 break;
707 case ECI_GENERAL_PURPOSE:
708 // Can't do anything with generic ECI; skip its 2 characters
709 codeIndex += 2;
710 break;
711 case ECI_USER_DEFINED:
712 // Can't do anything with user ECI; skip its 1 character
713 codeIndex++;
714 break;
715 case BEGIN_MACRO_PDF417_CONTROL_BLOCK:
716 status = DecodeMacroBlock(codewords, codeIndex, *resultMetadata, codeIndex);
717 break;
718 case BEGIN_MACRO_PDF417_OPTIONAL_FIELD:
719 case MACRO_PDF417_TERMINATOR:
720 // Should not see these outside a macro block
721 status = DecodeStatus::FormatError;
722 break;
723 default:
724 {
725 // Default to text compaction. During testing numerous barcodes
726 // appeared to be missing the starting mode. In these cases defaulting
727 // to text compaction seems to work.
728 codeIndex--;
729 std::string buf;
730 codeIndex = TextCompaction(codewords, codeIndex, buf);
731 TextDecoder::AppendLatin1(resultString, buf);
732 break;
733 }
734 }
735 if (codeIndex < (int)codewords.size()) {
736 code = codewords[codeIndex++];
737 }
738 else {
739 status = DecodeStatus::FormatError;
740 }
741 }
742 if (resultString.empty())
743 return DecodeStatus::FormatError;
744
745 if (StatusIsError(status))
746 return status;
747
748 return DecoderResult(ByteArray(), std::move(resultString))
749 .setEcLevel(std::to_wstring(ecLevel))
750 .setExtra(resultMetadata);
751}
752
753} // Pdf417
754} // ZXing
